< review>
I was worried when I read the reviews, but my experience was fine.
The website says ring them on arrival and they'll come and get you. Seems reasonable.  I rang, they came.  Took maybe 15 minutes but that's OK by me.  Of course instant would be great, but 15 is OK.

Picking up the car was easy.  Sign here, pay here, off you go.

Dropping off was just as easy.  What's the mileage, how much fuel is left over, off you go.

Waited about 10 minutes for shuttle back to airport.  No problems.

I may have just been lucky.  I had a very good experience, everything went smoothly which doesn't always happen.  But it worked for me.<//review>

After 3 more calls with no answer I had to call the 1-800 reservation line and they eventually connected me through to the office.  I was then informed that there is not shuttle that comes by at regular intervals but that I was supposed to call and request the shuttle.  The shuttle arrived about 20 minutes later.  The shuttle was not a bus like the other companies but was instead a dirty cargo van with seats.  I was then driven far away from the airport to the dirty run-down rental office.

At that point I was asked if I wouldn't mind driving one of their minivans.  I declined and stated that I would prefer to drive the vehicle that I had reserved.  (That was, not surprisingly, the reason that I reserved it!)  I was then told that the only vehicle available was a minivan.  Since it took so long to actually get to the office I did not have time to go to another company so I accepted the minivan.

Then the rental agent informed me that the tank had not been topped off.  Nevertheless she told me that I had to initial a portion of the rental contract that required me to return the vehicle with a full tank!  Luckily I am a lawyer and I read contracts before I sign them but the average person would probably just have initialled that provision of the contract.  I refused to initial the provision.  This was perhaps the most disturbing part of my experience.  Poor customer service and business management are one thing, but this was an intentional act of dishonesty and manipulation.  Obviously the intent was to take advantage of people who don't read the fine print of the rental contract.  This is not a trustworthy company.

After I refused to initial that portion of the contract I was told that I could take the van anyway.  I had to do a significant amount of driving and incurred extra expense due to driving a van rather than a small sedan.

My overall recommendation is to avoid this company.  It is not worth the headaches.  There are many other choices at the San Diego airport who offer much better customer service and reliability.< /review>< pictures>

< Name>
Courtney Ochi<//Name>
<time>1462037049240<//time><Rate>4<//Rate>< Text>
This place is awesome. It's got a laid back vibe like you're hanging out in a friend's garage. They've got couches, a ping pong table, Jenga (both giant and regular) and darts. Super laid back atmosphere to hang out and play some games. Not like your typical big breweries like Ballast or green flash.

The only thing was that the flight was a little pricey. Most places in the area have flights for $5-10. Their flights include 5 tasters for $15. You get a free glass which is nice, but definitely wasn't expecting it to be $15.<//Text>

<Rate>5</Rate><review>Although I live in Riverside I make regular visits to this outstanding small-but-expanding brewery in San Diego. Mike Hess offers a number of truly outstanding beers, including styles that are rarely seen on the west coast, e.g., Kolsch and Cream Ale. Their 11.3% Amplus Pale Ale (which drinks more like a triple IPA) is among my favorite brews of all time.

These are very, very nice folks making exceptional beer, even by the exacting standards of the San Diego beer market. I cannot recommend them highly enough!

And oh yes, Hess is dog-friendly!< /review><pics>None<//pics>< resp>

<user_id>107029944774793873532</user_id><name>Erin Kalendar</name><Date>1620149045906<//Date>< rating>
5</rating>
<text>Kirk park is great - large open field for sports or dogs playing fetch, separate but adjacent playgrounds for small kids and big kids. There are a few fun murals in between the buildings - the one of the many animals is extensive and fun for asking children to run to one section or another to find an animal. Nice path around the park for walking, as well as two full basketball courts in the back, adjacent to two horseshoe pits. Along the back fence line are huge cacti and some truly impressive redwoods. There is a bookable picnic area as well for parties and 2 bathrooms< /text>< Pictures>
None< /Pictures>

Very clean and quiet park. There is lots of open space for kids to bike. No creepy people. The picnic area is one of the best with lots of benches and decent shade. It has two unisex / family restrooms which I always find clean.< /Text>

<Review>I co-hosted a baby shower at Kirk Park and absolutely love the site. We are from out of town but the mother to be is from San Jose so we had to do it locally. The online pics don’t show a decent idea of the picnic are but it was enough to see it was all under trees.

It was perfect.

We didn’t use the BBQ pits so that was a non issue. We had 40 guests and more than enough space for them, games, food, and more.

The restrooms are right by the picnic area which the guests were thrilled about. Our 89 year old gramma (90 in two months) was so happy with the cleanliness of the restroom, it had seat covers, and soap and paper towels.

So many guests commented on what a perfect location for the event. Many of them had no idea this perfect little Park was so close to them.

I’m thankful we rented this facility and totally recommend it!< /Review><Pics>None</Pics>< Resp>

< Review>
I would like to recognize Sara (W?) and once again thank her for going above and beyond. Bass Lake was the first stop on our seven-day road trip. As luck would have it, we were headed out of town on a Sunday afternoon when our car started having battery trouble.
Sara promptly assisted me in purchasing a new battery and installed it quickly and effortlessly. She tested the battery and alternator and much to my dismay, the alternator tested bad. She did not have the alternator in stock but made a few calls and found it at the local competitor's shop.
Typically, I would install the alternator myself, but I was 300 miles from home and had five days left in my family's road trip.
Sara mentioned that there was a mobile mechanic nearby but wasn't sure if he worked on Sundays. She called him and set him up to come out and replace my alternator that same day. She even picked up the new alternator for me on her lunch break.
I'm not exaggerating when I say that Sara saved my summer vacation. She is a fine human being and is a true example customer service; something that is severely lacking in today's society.

Rich Hail, Sr. Digital Marketing Manager, SEMA<//Review>

< text>
The food was good enough for buffet food. The negative review was more based on the experience as a whole. The line moved extremely slow and I get that with covid precautions are in place. However, the cashier passed out gloves to people waiting in line to use when getting their food. My issue with this is that, by the time the people get up to pay, the gloves have been dropped on the floor, stuffed in pockets, kids using them to annoy each other, touching their face, people handling money and then they use the gloves to touch the serving spoons. Kinda makes the gloves pointless. They should be given after people pay and there should be extra gloves on the tables since gloves tear, get food on them, and get dropped. Once we were seated, I was able to see the person who was facilitating the seating standing talking to people who seemed to be friends or family members. All of a sudden the wait time to be seated made more sense. The final straw was the fact that there was someone allowed in who was clearly on something, was scratching himself while standing in the middle of the floor wearing no mask, yelling, and then walked up to the dessert buffet with no mask or gloves and stuck his hand in the dessert to pick something up with his fingers. We left right after and tipped our waitress extra for having to deal with the madness.<//text>

<rating>5< /rating><Text>This was our first time here, and for a Buffett restaurant it was very good! There was so much to select from, a full salad bar with not only green salads and toppings put other mixed salads like pasta, tuna, etc.  Over 4 different main course stations with freshly carved ribs, and sirloin steak grilled right in from of you, cooked the way you like it! And so many other main dish and side dish choices to mention. They also had a really fun dessert area, with most of the Staples you see at other buffets, chocolate cake & pudding, hello, cheesecakes, but also several types of cookies and brownies, a chocolate fountain with fresh strawberries, pineapple & rice crispy treats for dipping. Soft serve ice cream plus hand dipped ice cream with several flavors and even a cotton candy machine! All you can drink soft drinks, horchata, iced teas & coffee. They also have early bird discounts & a  seniors discount. Definitely well worth the cost and our waitress who picked up our plates and served us more drinks was very nice and plates never stayed on our table while we were making additional choices of food. I would go back. < review>
Very clean, the staff is very nice and helpful.
Everything in good condition, considering certain places are opening back up for dine in due to the Covid-19 pandemic.
Masks are required to enter and while walking around to get your food, by the way the staff serves you so no one is actually allowed to serve them sleves, keeping everything more sanitary and safe for everyone.
We went on 6/17/2020 adults price is $18.27 and kids under 9 are $8.25 I think, cents are a little off butbadukts are $18 and some change and children are $8 and some change if under 9 years of age.
Food is delicious, chicken baked and fried are cooked to perfection. Salad bar is good and the ham also it's really tender.
We enjoyed ourselves, except for the ice cream machine, it wasn't working...bug bummer for the kids.
Overall it was all good!< /review>

Yesterday was my second time visiting the Golden Corral Buffet in Bellflower. My first experience was great. The food was better than most buffets I been to and it was kept clan from what I could see.

My second visit, which was yesterday, not so much! I went for dinner with my hubby and everything was going well until my second round of getting food. When I returned to the table, sat down, then pulled a napkin out of the dispenser on our table and layed it on the table, a TINY BABY ROACH crawled from under it!!!!! We didn't get loud and crazy, I killed it with the napkin, then called over the manager that was on the floor to inform him. The manager went on to tell us how sorry he was and that they had spraid the restaurant the night before, as if that was acceptable. I mean really, a BABY ROACH on your table while you're eating!!!! He took the napkin and about 5 minutes later brought us a coupon for 50% off or next visit!!! SERIOUSLY? Needless to say, we threw the coupon away and will not be going back.

So, if you choose to go there to eat, LOOK OUT FOR THE BABY ROACHES!!!!</Text>

<date>1569210218319<//date>< rate>
4</rate>
<Text>I watched this place being built, taking over the old used car lot. Over time, I became intrigued what it would become.

When I saw the sign go up, I discovered it was this buffet. I'm not a big buffet fan. I read descriptions that compared this place to Hometown. I REALLY don't like Hometown.

Our visit here was for my birthday, and was a bit of a gag, as I had mentioned this place a lot while it was being built. "Get it out of your system, finally!"

Down to brass tacks; the food was very good, surprisingly good. The bang for the buck is great. There were two dishes I was disappointed with (I'm not a big fan of fried foods, so can't comment on those). The Brussels sprouts were mushy, and the... shoot, I can't remember the other.

The reduction in one star is more about traffic control than the food. The amount of people that come through is pretty intense. The walkways can bottleneck, and create uncomfortable situations. Noise levels can get pretty high too.

Overall it was a good experience, with surprisingly good food for a buffet. Good value too!</Text><Pictures>None< /Pictures><Response>{'time': 1570163662868, 'text': "We'll turn those 4 stars into 5 when you visit next, Russell! < text>
The Golden Corral in Bellflower, California is the ultimate buffet dining experience. They offer a wide selection of entrees, side dishes, salads and desserts. Their food is excellent quality and absolutely delicious. If you want sirloin steak they'll cook it right in front of you. Just tell them how you want it-rare medium or well-done. And last but certainly not least, the manager and his staff are very attentive to their customers and friendly. And if it happens to be your birthday, six or seven of them will gather around your table and sing you happy birthday. We highly recommend this buffet restaurant.</text>

Haven’t been in awhile and we enjoyed this visit. Happened to be a seafood week and we enjoyed the catfish and shrimp kabobs. The steak was tender and grilled to your liking. There was prime rib and several fish plates including salmon. The crowd of people guaranteed fresh food as workers were constantly renewing the many dishes to choose from. This place is very popular with a good line of people waiting to get seated.
We liked the food we had good waiters and waitresses and never felt that the place was unkempt.< /review>

<Rate>5< /Rate>< review>
Honestly, for how many customers there were, the food was fantastic. Especially for a buffet. I am planning on coming again. The only thing that I will say annoyed me is the waiter. What's the point of the waiter if she didn't clear our plates or give us refills? I would have been happier doing it myself.

Still though, the food was very good. Not one complaint about anything that I decided to grab. Including the amazing steak. Very good place if you're looking for a buffet. Worth every cent.

Also the rest of the staff was very lovely.</review>

This place is awesome! All kinds of different drinks to choose from except alcoholic beverages. Full salad bar. Went on a Friday night in December 2017 and almost walked right in. I'm used to this place being packed but it wasn't so bad. Maybe people are finally getting tired of it or something. The food selection is good but.... It is a fight just to get food. When I went it was a mad house. It was early on a weekday night and the line was out the door and around the corner. Once we were in then began the struggle to get food. There is no such thing as a line here. The staff member told me to "get in where I fit in". I have been to countless buffets and have never encountered such a stressful experience trying to get my food. I wouldn't recommend it.</Text>

< Review>
We had a party of 24 that came to celebrate(all family). The cashier(can't remember her name)did an excellent job..she was very friendly, attentive, and was a model employee. She is why this place got any stars. The other employees Tyler kept coming to our table counting how many people were in our party and kept saying we didn't pay for someone. We had our receipts on the table plain as day to show them we paid for everyone. Then a few mins later here comes Abigail counting people again..she did this about 3 times. So we asked her why do you keep coming back here counting we paid for everyone. She stated, "oh I was making sure you were sitting at the right table". She could have come with the truth and just said I'm here to count your party for the 3rd time(8 total between her and Tyler). I ask to speak to the manager. Here comes this large man Xavier(manager)who literally pushes Abigail aside and is now in my face. Tyler had already spoken to him so he knows what they were doing and he is condoning it. I tell him that they are making us feel like criminals or if we did something wrong when they keep coming counting everyone in our party. He went on to tell me that that's their job and they're going to keep doing it. I told him once is doing your job 8 times they are stereotyping(we are Blacks and Mexicans). He said with a bad attitude so what do you want me to do. Do you want your money back? I then told him he is not representing the company/ franchise properly and the customers always right. He said No the customers not..no their not always right!! He believes that we did bring someone in without paying until they finally got the count right. I was floored at the way he(manager) conducted himself. He needs to be demoted. He was completely rude. I told him I was calling corporate and could I have the number? He points to a number on the wall. As soon as he walked away from us he jumps on to his laptop and starts typing and looking at us. We will Not be returning no matter how good the food was.< /Review>

<user_id>104636687373132435944<//user_id><Text>Busy. Busy. Busy.  Expect a 30-45 minute wait just to get inside.  Once inside, you feel not golden but corralled.  As I was winding around their line inside, the Disneyfication of eating could not be escaped.

In terms of food, the quality of ingredients is the same as any other buffet.  What makes them distinct is the processing and preparation of said foods.  Batch processing is the name of the game.  Do not expect culinary art.  If all you want to do is get your fill, then this is the place for you.

Dinner is $12.99/pp; drinks are an extra $1.99.< /Text><Gmap_id>0x80dd32bcc89aedc9:0xabbcb4d9de44431</Gmap_id><time>1452565009560< /time><Rating>3</Rating><user_name>Jeannette G.<//user_name>< response>

<gmapID>0x80dd32bcc89aedc9:0xabbcb4d9de44431</gmapID><time>1485597642575</time><Rating>4<//Rating><user_name>Chhan Hak< /user_name><review>One of two Golden Corrals within about 20 miles of the Long Beach/Southbay area. I believe the other one is in Downey.

Came in for dinner on a Friday, four adults, the total(with drinks) came out to $75(+$10 tip for our waitress).

Surprisingly, we didn't have to wait. There was only one party ahead of us. Usually, there is a 15/20min wait, according to my cousins, who dined with me, it was my first time.

The selection was absolutely immense. Seafood, sides, soups, meats. As well, your average salad bar. All your typical great American entrees. Plus, there is a huge dessert selection. Pies, cookies, ice cream. I really enjoyed their meat selection, there was prime rib and various steak cuts[cooked/sliced to your liking(medium-rare, rare, etc)].

The food was enjoyable, a bit salty but Americans don't have a sodium problem. The drawbacks are the seating (it can be a bit cramped) and the lines for the food, might have to wait a few extra minutes to get your servings.

Would definitely come again, the value is great for the amount of food you can get.</review><resp>None</resp></record>
